2. Elastic force, or the power of recoil, arises from the bending ol rigid bodies inasmuch as these when bent strive to return to their original form. And indeed it is probable that the elasticity of the air results mainly from this very cause. It would certainly be reasonable to suppose that nitro-aerial and fiery par· ticles are fixed in the a'e'rial particles themselves and constitute the more active part of them.
